      • Payment

        public Payment(double a,
               PaymentMethod pm,
               java.util.Date d,
               User c)
        This is the constructor of the class.
        name: Payment.
        pre: the variables c, d, pm, a, are already initialized.
        post: the attributes and relationships of the class have been initialized.
        Parameters:
        c - Is a User object that references the user creator of the payment. c!=null
        pm - Is a PaymentMethod variable that contains the payment method of the payment. pm== EFECTIVO, pm==TARJETA_DE_DEBITO, pm==TARJETA_DE_CREDITO, or pm==TRANSFERENCIA_BANCARIA
        d - Is a Date variable that contains the date of the creation of the payment. d!=null
        a - Is a double variable that contains the value of the payment.
